<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Taskbar: Icons missing / vanishing]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7580&amp;p=32929#p32929"><![CDATA[
I too have been experiencing the vanishing icons and specifically problems with Chrome. For me this happened when I was updated to the Creator's version of Windows 10. <br /><br />I found that in all but Chrome, if I pinned from the actual executable, I could get the program's icon to stick, but then I would get duplicate icons on the right side of the taskbar as I loaded the program. This is something I have reported in the Windows Community Forum, as I think it is related to Creator as the duplicate Icons as appear when in safe mode... i.e. not Classic Shell. The loss of the Chrome Icon occurs after a cold shutdown and subsequent reboot. I suspect that is also a Windows issue, though it might not be. It may be a difference in how Windows Interacts with Shell during the pinning process as per Creator.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20688">MikeLieberman</a> — Thu Jun 08, 2017 7:04 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
