<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7580&amp;p=32636#p32636"><![CDATA[
Hi,<br /><br />I tried for some days now, but things didn't change: It may be unlikely, but with classic shell installed in fact the pinned Chrome icon gets lost from the taskbar. For that, you don't even need a reboot -- logging out the user and logging in again is sufficient to let the icon vanish.<br /><br />Without classic shell, the pinned icon keeps being pinned as it should. When I re-install classic shell, the icon runs up and away again, sometimes immediately at the next booting, sometimes at the second one.<br /><br />Even extremely unlikely things love to happen quite fast...<br /><br />What can I do to help finding out possible reasons?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=19816">njotha</a> — Sat May 13, 2017 12:04 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
