<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7580&amp;p=32524#p32524"><![CDATA[
O/S: Windows 10 Version 1703 Build 15063.138<br /><br />Classic Shell version 4.3.0 German<br /><br />No antivirus (except Windows Defender), no adblocker or similar apps installed<br /><br />Hardware: Intel NUC6i7kyk, 16 G Ram, 256 G m.2 ssd for O/S and software, 1 T ssd for data only<br /><br />Several efforts to help myself: cleaned/resetted icon cache etc including re-installing Win 10.<br /><br />Problem: With Classic Shell installed, some icons in taskbar get totally lost after rebooting, not even the famous &quot;white square&quot; remains:<br /><br />a) Google Chrome&#058; gets absolutely lost, even if you uninstall CS, reboot, add Chrome to the taskbar, reboot, re-install CS - after one to three reboots, Chrome again has vanished from the taskbar. As long as CS is not installed, the Chrome icon behaves normally in the taskbar.<br /><br />b) Office 2016: Icons get lost similarily to Chrome, but do so only if you move a link to Word/Excel etc to the taskbar (e.g. a link which you had at your desktop). It doesn't get lost any more when you open the office programme directory and pin the .exe directly to the taskbar.<br /><br />c) No problem with internal Windows apps / links resp., they behave normal in taskbar (Camera, &quot;This PC&quot;, &quot;Show Desktop&quot;, Edge, Calculator, Snipping tool etc.)<br /><br />I'd really like to have Chrome and others available at the taskbar again...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=19816">njotha</a> — Sat May 06, 2017 9:36 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
